---
name: array-companion-statics
---

# `Array.fill/tabulate/range/empty` route to the List companion on the JS backend

Regression for the JS backend (busi deep-offline standalone bundle, surfaced by
`tests/v2/qr.ssc`). `Array(...)` is emitted as a JS array literal, so the bare
`Array` value at a `_dispatch` site is the *native* `Array` constructor, which
lacks the Scala collection statics. `Array.fill(n)(x)` (and `tabulate`/`range`/
`empty`) therefore threw `Method not found`. Since List/Seq/Array share one JS
array representation, `_dispatch` now routes these statics to the `List`
companion, whose result is the correct runtime value.

```scalascript
println(Array.fill(3)(7).sum)
println(Array.fill(2)("ab").mkString)
println(Array.tabulate(4)(i => i * i).mkString(","))
println(Array.range(0, 5).mkString("-"))
println(Array.empty[Int].length)
```
